    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-06-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-06-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="350"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d350">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">150.071 Control/205</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Chief of the Division of Western European
                        Affairs</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Moffat</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-06-13">June 13,
                            1935</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Netherland Minister called this afternoon to renew his protest against the
                    King-Dies Bill. I got in touch with Mr. Simmons, of the Visa Division, who
                    informed me that the Bill had been favorably reported to the Senate and to the
                    House on June 10. He said the Department had reiterated its opposition and that
                    Mr. Carr<note n="10" xml:id="d350fn10">Wilbur J. Carr, Assistant Secretary of
                        State.</note> had as in the past testified against it. We could not predict
                    the ultimate fate but we must bear in mind that this session will last through
                    next-year and that the measure was liable to be called to the floor at any time.
                    The Minister remarked that in that case everything possible would appear to have
                    been done but that the Bill, if passed, would have disastrous results on their
                    shipping.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Pierrepont Moffat</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
